SIMPLE: annulus
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Annulus
<hw>An"nu*lus</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Annuli</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A ring; a ringlike part or space.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A space contained
between the circumferences of two circles, one within the other.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The solid formed by a circle revolving around a line
which is the plane of the circle but does not cut it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Ring-shaped structures or
markings, found in, or upon, various animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Annumerate</ent>⟦br⟧
